n the SFI convolutional layer has stride S, its input\n˜ in\nis interpreted as a virtual sequence sampled with period ∆\ntok (S):\n˜ in\n˜ out\n∆\ntok (S) = ∆tok /S.\n\n(1)\n\n˜ in\nThis virtual input sampling period ∆\ntok (S) is used as the sampling\nperiod provided to the weight-generation module of the SFI layers.\nThe kernel size is also adjusted on this virtual time scale. Let\nKbase be the kernel size when S = 1. For stride S, the kernel size\nis given by\nK(S) = Kbase S.\n(2)\n\nTTR [ms]\n\nToken frame rate [Hz]\n\nK [sample]\n\nS [sample]\n\n13.3\n26.7\n40.0\n53.3\n66.7\n106.7\n133.3", "stderr": "\nShell cwd was reset to /inspire/qb-ilm/project/video-generation/chenxie-25019/hyr/iHateTheWorld555.github.io", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
